<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-955-558  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 955 558.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions On Information Systems  July 1989 v7 n3 p246(25).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Knowledge-based search tactics for an intelligent intermediarysystem. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smith, Philip J.; Shute, Steven J.; Galdes, Deb; Chignell, Mark H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Domain-knowledge-based strategies for searching bibliographicdatabases are incorporated into EP-X, a semantically based,computerized search intermediary.andP;  Bibliographic databasesearchers often need help in defining or optimizing their searchstrategies and queries, the latter consisting of a series ofkeywords connected by logical operators such as AND, OR and NOT.andO;EP-X was developed as a semantically based search tool for usewith the Chemical Abstracts database.andP;  The design of EP-X focuseson semantic-level communication between the user and theintermediary and the provision of assistance in identifying andresolving ambiguities.andP;  Nineteen knowledge-based search tacticswere identified that facilitate change in the definition of topicand increase the thoroughness of a search.andP;  Development,functioning and application of EP-X are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Knowledge-Based SystemsSemanticsDocument Management SystemsInformation Storage and RetrievalTheoretical ResearchSearch StrategyBibliographic Data BasesNew TechniqueSearching.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Partial network of associate concepts. (chart)Entry and interpretation of keyword phrases. (chart)Rule evaluation tree. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>